#compdef letmein
# ============================================================================
# _letmein — zsh completion for **letmein** — mbuesch/letmein, the
#             pure-Rust **authenticated port-knocking client + server**.
#             Lets a network operator close every inbound port on a
#             server's firewall by default, then re-open specific
#             ports (or jump-routing rules) on-demand via a
#             cryptographically authenticated "knock" handshake
#             between the `letmein` client and the `letmeind` server
#             daemon — the modern replacement for legacy port-
#             knocking tools (knockd, fwknop, dnsknock) with proper
#             challenge-response authentication instead of replay-
#             vulnerable sequence-knocking, full IPv4 + IPv6
#             support, full Linux + nftables + iptables backends
#             via the bundled `letmeinfwd` firewall driver, and
#             optional seccomp sandboxing of the client + server
#             processes.  Rust=176 OPENING leg of new Axis 121
#             (DNS / IETF RFC-1035 + DoT (RFC-7858) + DoH
#             (RFC-8484) + DoQ (RFC-9250) name-resolution
#             protocol) via the canonical Rust DNS library
#             **hickory-dns/hickory-resolver** (formerly
#             trust-dns-resolver — the de-facto Rust DNS
#             resolver maintained by the Hickory DNS team).
# ============================================================================
#
# UPSTREAM
