#                  (workspace member: letmein/ — the client bin;
#                   sibling crates `letmeind` (the server daemon),
#                   `letmeinfwd` (the firewall driver),
#                   `letmein-proto` (the wire protocol),
#                   `letmein-conf` (the YAML config layer),
#                   `letmein-seccomp` (the seccomp sandbox), and
#                   `letmein-systemd` (the systemd integration)
#                   are all in the same Cargo workspace)
#   Maintainer : Michael Büsch  (m@bues.ch; long-standing Linux
#                 kernel contributor — original maintainer of the
#                 b43 Broadcom wireless driver and the bcm-2835-
#                 wireless-link firmware; multiple Rust security-
#                 tooling projects)
#   License    : Apache-2.0 OR MIT  (dual-licensed)
#   Stars      : 51
#   Language   : Rust  (clap-derive for the CLI surface +
#                 tokio for the async runtime + hickory-resolver
#                 for DNS-over-TLS / DNS-over-HTTPS / DNS-over-
#                 QUIC name resolution + dns-lookup (the
